{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'd like to start with a couple of quick examples."},{"time":3000,"text":"These are spinneret glands"},{"time":5000,"text":"on the abdomen of a spider."},{"time":7000,"text":"They produce six different types of silk, which is spun together into a fiber,"},{"time":10000,"text":"tougher than any fiber humans have ever made."},{"time":13000,"text":"The nearest we've come is with aramid fiber."},{"time":16000,"text":"And to make that, it involves extremes of temperature,"},{"time":18000,"text":"extremes of pressure and loads of pollution."},{"time":21000,"text":"And yet the spider manages to do it at ambient temperature and pressure"},{"time":24000,"text":"with raw materials of dead flies and water."},{"time":27000,"text":"It does suggest we've still got a bit to learn."},{"time":29000,"text":"This beetle can detect a forest fire at 80 kilometers away."},{"time":32000,"text":"That's roughly 10,000 times the range"},{"time":34000,"text":"of man-made fire detectors."},{"time":36000,"text":"And what's more, this guy doesn't need a wire"},{"time":38000,"text":"connected all the way back to a power station burning fossil fuels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"So these two examples give a sense of what biomimicry can deliver."},{"time":45000,"text":"If we could learn to make things and do things the way nature does,"},{"time":48000,"text":"we could achieve factor 10, factor 100,"},{"time":50000,"text":"maybe even factor 1,000 savings"},{"time":52000,"text":"in resource and energy use."},{"time":55000,"text":"And if we're to make progress with the sustainability revolution,"},{"time":58000,"text":"I believe there are three really big changes"},{"time":60000,"text":"we need to bring about."},{"time":62000,"text":"Firstly, radical increases in resource efficiency."},{"time":65000,"text":"Secondly, shifting from a linear, wasteful,"},{"time":67000,"text":"polluting way of using resources"},{"time":69000,"text":"to a closed-loop model."},{"time":71000,"text":"And thirdly, changing from a fossil fuel economy"},{"time":73000,"text":"to a solar economy."},{"time":75000,"text":"And for all three of these, I believe,"},{"time":77000,"text":"biomimicry has a lot of the solutions that we're going to need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"You could look at nature as being like a catalog of products,"},{"time":82000,"text":"and all of those have benefited"},{"time":84000,"text":"from a 3.8-billion-year research and development period."},{"time":87000,"text":"And given that level of investment, it makes sense to use it."},{"time":90000,"text":"So I'm going to talk about some projects that have explored these ideas."},{"time":93000,"text":"And let's start with radical increases"},{"time":95000,"text":"in resource efficiency."},{"time":97000,"text":"When we were working on the Eden Project,"},{"time":99000,"text":"we had to create a very large greenhouse"},{"time":101000,"text":"in a site that was not only irregular,"},{"time":103000,"text":"but it was continually changing because it was still being quarried."},{"time":106000,"text":"It was a hell of a challenge,"},{"time":108000,"text":"and it was actually examples from biology"},{"time":110000,"text":"that provided a lot of the clues."},{"time":112000,"text":"So for instance,"},{"time":114000,"text":"it was soap bubbles that helped us generate a building form"},{"time":116000,"text":"that would work regardless of the final ground levels."},{"time":119000,"text":"Studying pollen grains"},{"time":121000,"text":"and radiolaria and carbon molecules"},{"time":123000,"text":"helped us devise the most efficient structural solution"},{"time":126000,"text":"using hexagons and pentagons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129000,"text":"The next move was that we wanted"},{"time":131000,"text":"to try and maximize the size of those hexagons."},{"time":133000,"text":"And to do that we had to find an alternative to glass,"},{"time":135000,"text":"which is really very limited in terms of its unit sizes."},{"time":138000,"text":"And in nature there are lots of examples"},{"time":141000,"text":"of very efficient structures based on pressurized membranes."},{"time":144000,"text":"So we started exploring this material called ETFE."},{"time":147000,"text":"It's a high-strength polymer."},{"time":149000,"text":"And what you do is you put it together in three layers,"},{"time":151000,"text":"you weld it around the edge, and then you inflate it."},{"time":154000,"text":"And the great thing about this stuff"},{"time":156000,"text":"is you can make it in units"},{"time":158000,"text":"of roughly seven times the size of glass,"},{"time":160000,"text":"and it was only one percent of the weight of double-glazing."},{"time":162000,"text":"So that was a factor-100 saving."},{"time":164000,"text":"And what we found is that we got into a positive cycle"},{"time":167000,"text":"in which one breakthrough facilitated another."},{"time":169000,"text":"So with such large, lightweight pillows,"},{"time":172000,"text":"we had much less steel."},{"time":174000,"text":"With less steel we were getting more sunlight in,"},{"time":176000,"text":"which meant we didn't have to put as much extra heat in winter."},{"time":179000,"text":"And with less overall weight in the superstructure,"},{"time":181000,"text":"there were big savings in the foundations."},{"time":183000,"text":"And at the end of the project we worked out"},{"time":185000,"text":"that the weight of that superstructure"},{"time":187000,"text":"was actually less than the weight of the air inside the building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"So I think the Eden Project is a fairly good example"},{"time":193000,"text":"of how ideas from biology"},{"time":195000,"text":"can lead to radical increases in resource efficiency --"},{"time":198000,"text":"delivering the same function,"},{"time":200000,"text":"but with a fraction of the resource input."},{"time":202000,"text":"And actually there are loads of examples in nature"},{"time":204000,"text":"that you could turn to for similar solutions."},{"time":207000,"text":"So for instance, you could develop super-efficient roof structures"},{"time":210000,"text":"based on giant Amazon water lilies,"},{"time":213000,"text":"whole buildings inspired by abalone shells,"},{"time":215000,"text":"super-lightweight bridges inspired by plant cells."},{"time":218000,"text":"There's a world of beauty and efficiency to explore here"},{"time":221000,"text":"using nature as a design tool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"So now I want to go onto talking about the linear-to-closed-loop idea."},{"time":227000,"text":"The way we tend to use resources"},{"time":229000,"text":"is we extract them,"},{"time":231000,"text":"we turn them into short-life products and then dispose of them."},{"time":233000,"text":"Nature works very differently."},{"time":235000,"text":"In ecosystems, the waste from one organism"},{"time":237000,"text":"becomes the nutrient for something else in that system."},{"time":239000,"text":"And there are some examples of projects"},{"time":241000,"text":"that have deliberately tried to mimic ecosystems."},{"time":244000,"text":"And one of my favorites"},{"time":246000,"text":"is called the Cardboard to Caviar Project"},{"time":248000,"text":"by Graham Wiles."},{"time":250000,"text":"And in their area they had a lot of shops and restaurants"},{"time":253000,"text":"that were producing lots of food, cardboard and plastic waste."},{"time":256000,"text":"It was ending up in landfills."},{"time":258000,"text":"Now the really clever bit is what they did with the cardboard waste."},{"time":260000,"text":"And I'm just going to talk through this animation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263000,"text":"So they were paid to collect it from the restaurants."},{"time":265000,"text":"They then shredded the cardboard"},{"time":267000,"text":"and sold it to equestrian centers as horse bedding."},{"time":270000,"text":"When that was soiled, they were paid again to collect it."},{"time":272000,"text":"They put it into worm recomposting systems,"},{"time":274000,"text":"which produced a lot of worms, which they fed to Siberian sturgeon,"},{"time":277000,"text":"which produced caviar, which they sold back to the restaurants."},{"time":280000,"text":"So it transformed a linear process"},{"time":282000,"text":"into a closed-loop model,"},{"time":284000,"text":"and it created more value in the process."},{"time":287000,"text":"Graham Wiles has continued to add more and more elements to this,"},{"time":289000,"text":"turning waste streams into schemes that create value."},{"time":292000,"text":"And just as natural systems"},{"time":294000,"text":"tend to increase in diversity and resilience over time,"},{"time":297000,"text":"there's a real sense with this project"},{"time":299000,"text":"that the number of possibilities"},{"time":302000,"text":"just continue increasing."},{"time":304000,"text":"And I know it's a quirky example,"},{"time":306000,"text":"but I think the implications of this are quite radical,"},{"time":308000,"text":"because it suggests that we could actually"},{"time":310000,"text":"transform a big problem -- waste -- into a massive opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"And particularly in cities --"},{"time":315000,"text":"we could look at the whole metabolism of cities,"},{"time":317000,"text":"and look at those as opportunities."},{"time":319000,"text":"And that's what we're doing on the next project I'm going to talk about,"},{"time":321000,"text":"the Mobius Project,"},{"time":323000,"text":"where we're trying to bring together a number of activities,"},{"time":325000,"text":"all within one building,"},{"time":327000,"text":"so that the waste from one can be the nutrient for another."},{"time":330000,"text":"And the kind of elements I'm talking about"},{"time":332000,"text":"are, firstly, we have a restaurant inside a productive greenhouse,"},{"time":335000,"text":"a bit like this one in Amsterdam called De Kas."},{"time":337000,"text":"Then we would have an anaerobic digester,"},{"time":339000,"text":"which could deal with all the biodegradable waste from the local area,"},{"time":342000,"text":"turn that into heat for the greenhouse"},{"time":344000,"text":"and electricity to feed back into the grid."},{"time":346000,"text":"We'd have a water treatment system"},{"time":348000,"text":"treating wastewater, turning that into fresh water"},{"time":350000,"text":"and generating energy from the solids"},{"time":352000,"text":"using just plants and micro-organisms."},{"time":355000,"text":"We'd have a fish farm fed with vegetable waste from the kitchen"},{"time":357000,"text":"and worms from the compost"},{"time":359000,"text":"and supplying fish back to the restaurant."},{"time":361000,"text":"And we'd also have a coffee shop, and the waste grains from that"},{"time":364000,"text":"could be used as a substrate for growing mushrooms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366000,"text":"So you can see that we're bringing together"},{"time":368000,"text":"cycles of food, energy and water and waste"},{"time":370000,"text":"all within one building."},{"time":372000,"text":"And just for fun, we've proposed this for a roundabout in central London,"},{"time":375000,"text":"which at the moment is a complete eyesore."},{"time":377000,"text":"Some of you may recognize this."},{"time":379000,"text":"And with just a little bit of planning,"},{"time":381000,"text":"we could transform a space dominated by traffic"},{"time":384000,"text":"into one that provides open space for people,"},{"time":387000,"text":"reconnects people with food"},{"time":389000,"text":"and transforms waste into closed loop opportunities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392000,"text":"So the final project I want to talk about"},{"time":394000,"text":"is the Sahara Forest Project, which we're working on at the moment."},{"time":397000,"text":"It may come as a surprise to some of you"},{"time":399000,"text":"to hear that quite large areas of what are currently desert"},{"time":401000,"text":"were actually forested a fairly short time ago."},{"time":404000,"text":"So for instance, when Julius Caesar arrived in North Africa,"},{"time":407000,"text":"huge areas of North Africa"},{"time":409000,"text":"were covered in cedar and cypress forests."},{"time":412000,"text":"And during the evolution of life on the Earth,"},{"time":414000,"text":"it was the colonization"},{"time":416000,"text":"of the land by plants"},{"time":418000,"text":"that helped create the benign climate we currently enjoy."},{"time":420000,"text":"The converse is also true."},{"time":422000,"text":"The more vegetation we lose,"},{"time":424000,"text":"the more that's likely to exacerbate climate change"},{"time":426000,"text":"and lead to further desertification."},{"time":429000,"text":"And this animation,"},{"time":431000,"text":"this shows photosynthetic activity over the course of a number of years,"},{"time":434000,"text":"and what you can see is that the boundaries of those deserts"},{"time":437000,"text":"shift quite a lot,"},{"time":439000,"text":"and that raises the question"},{"time":441000,"text":"of whether we can intervene at the boundary conditions"},{"time":444000,"text":"to halt, or maybe even reverse, desertification."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"And if you look at some of the organisms"},{"time":449000,"text":"that have evolved to live in deserts,"},{"time":451000,"text":"there are some amazing examples of adaptations to water scarcity."},{"time":454000,"text":"This is the Namibian fog-basking beetle,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and it's evolved a way of harvesting its own fresh water in a desert."},{"time":459000,"text":"The way it does this is it comes out at night,"},{"time":461000,"text":"crawls to the top of a sand dune,"},{"time":463000,"text":"and because it's got a matte black shell,"},{"time":465000,"text":"is able to radiate heat out to the night sky"},{"time":467000,"text":"and become slightly cooler than its surroundings."},{"time":469000,"text":"So when the moist breeze blows in off the sea,"},{"time":471000,"text":"you get these droplets of water forming on the beetle's shell."},{"time":474000,"text":"Just before sunrise, he tips his shell up, the water runs down into his mouth,"},{"time":477000,"text":"has a good drink, goes off and hides for the rest of the day."},{"time":479000,"text":"And the ingenuity, if you could call it that,"},{"time":481000,"text":"goes even further."},{"time":483000,"text":"Because if you look closely at the beetle's shell,"},{"time":485000,"text":"there are lots of little bumps on that shell."},{"time":487000,"text":"And those bumps are hydrophilic; they attract water."},{"time":490000,"text":"Between them there's a waxy finish which repels water."},{"time":493000,"text":"And the effect of this is that"},{"time":495000,"text":"as the droplets start to form on the bumps,"},{"time":497000,"text":"they stay in tight, spherical beads,"},{"time":499000,"text":"which means they're much more mobile"},{"time":501000,"text":"than they would be if it was just a film of water over the whole beetle's shell."},{"time":504000,"text":"So even when there's only a small amount of moisture in the air,"},{"time":507000,"text":"it's able to harvest that very effectively and channel it down to its mouth."},{"time":510000,"text":"So amazing example of an adaptation"},{"time":512000,"text":"to a very resource-constrained environment --"},{"time":514000,"text":"and in that sense, very relevant"},{"time":516000,"text":"to the kind of challenges we're going to be facing"},{"time":518000,"text":"over the next few years, next few decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"We're working with the guy who invented the Seawater Greenhouse."},{"time":522000,"text":"This is a greenhouse designed for arid coastal regions,"},{"time":525000,"text":"and the way it works is that you have this whole wall of evaporator grills,"},{"time":529000,"text":"and you trickle seawater over that"},{"time":531000,"text":"so that wind blows through, it picks up a lot of moisture"},{"time":533000,"text":"and is cooled in the process."},{"time":535000,"text":"So inside it's cool and humid,"},{"time":537000,"text":"which means the plants need less water to grow."},{"time":539000,"text":"And then at the back of the greenhouse,"},{"time":541000,"text":"it condenses a lot of that humidity as freshwater"},{"time":544000,"text":"in a process that is effectively identical to the beetle."},{"time":547000,"text":"And what they found with the first Seawater Greenhouse that was built"},{"time":550000,"text":"was it was producing slightly more freshwater"},{"time":552000,"text":"than it needed for the plants inside."},{"time":555000,"text":"So they just started spreading this on the land around,"},{"time":558000,"text":"and the combination of that and the elevated humidity"},{"time":560000,"text":"had quite a dramatic effect on the local area."},{"time":563000,"text":"This photograph was taken on completion day,"},{"time":565000,"text":"and just one year later, it looked like that."},{"time":567000,"text":"So it was like a green inkblot spreading out from the building"},{"time":570000,"text":"turning barren land back into biologically productive land --"},{"time":573000,"text":"and in that sense, going beyond sustainable design"},{"time":575000,"text":"to achieve restorative design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577000,"text":"So we were keen to scale this up"},{"time":579000,"text":"and apply biomimicry ideas to maximize the benefits."},{"time":582000,"text":"And when you think about nature,"},{"time":584000,"text":"often you think about it as being all about competition."},{"time":586000,"text":"But actually in mature ecosystems,"},{"time":588000,"text":"you're just as likely to find examples"},{"time":590000,"text":"of symbiotic relationships."},{"time":592000,"text":"So an important biomimicry principle"},{"time":594000,"text":"is to find ways of bringing technologies together"},{"time":596000,"text":"in symbiotic clusters."},{"time":598000,"text":"And the technology that we settled on"},{"time":600000,"text":"as an ideal partner for the Seawater Greenhouse"},{"time":602000,"text":"is concentrated solar power,"},{"time":604000,"text":"which uses solar-tracking mirrors to focus the sun's heat"},{"time":606000,"text":"to create electricity."},{"time":608000,"text":"And just to give you some sense of the potential of CSP,"},{"time":611000,"text":"consider that we receive"},{"time":613000,"text":"10,000 times as much energy from the sun every year"},{"time":616000,"text":"as we use in energy from all forms --"},{"time":618000,"text":"10,000 times."},{"time":620000,"text":"So our energy problems are not intractable."},{"time":622000,"text":"It's a challenge to our ingenuity."},{"time":624000,"text":"And the kind of synergies I'm talking about"},{"time":626000,"text":"are, firstly, both these technologies work very well in hot, sunny deserts."},{"time":630000,"text":"CSP needs a supply of demineralized freshwater."},{"time":633000,"text":"That's exactly what the Seawater Greenhouse produces."},{"time":635000,"text":"CSP produces a lot of waste heat."},{"time":637000,"text":"We'll be able to make use of all that to evaporate more seawater"},{"time":640000,"text":"and enhance the restorative benefits."},{"time":642000,"text":"And finally, in the shade under the mirrors,"},{"time":644000,"text":"it's possible to grow all sorts of crops"},{"time":646000,"text":"that would not grow in direct sunlight."},{"time":648000,"text":"So this is how this scheme would look."},{"time":650000,"text":"The idea is we create this long hedge of greenhouses facing the wind."},{"time":653000,"text":"We'd have concentrated solar power plants"},{"time":655000,"text":"at intervals along the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657000,"text":"Some of you might be wondering what we would do with all the salts."},{"time":660000,"text":"And with biomimicry, if you've got an underutilized resource,"},{"time":663000,"text":"you don't think, \"How am I going to dispose of this?\""},{"time":665000,"text":"You think, \"What can I add to the system to create more value?\""},{"time":668000,"text":"And it turns out"},{"time":670000,"text":"that different things crystallize out at different stages."},{"time":672000,"text":"When you evaporate seawater, the first thing to crystallize out"},{"time":674000,"text":"is calcium carbonate."},{"time":676000,"text":"And that builds up on the evaporators --"},{"time":678000,"text":"and that's what that image on the left is --"},{"time":680000,"text":"gradually getting encrusted with the calcium carbonate."},{"time":682000,"text":"So after a while, we could take that out,"},{"time":684000,"text":"use it as a lightweight building block."},{"time":686000,"text":"And if you think about the carbon in that,"},{"time":688000,"text":"that would have come out of the atmosphere, into the sea"},{"time":690000,"text":"and then locked away in a building product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692000,"text":"The next thing is sodium chloride."},{"time":694000,"text":"You can also compress that into a building block,"},{"time":696000,"text":"as they did here."},{"time":698000,"text":"This is a hotel in Bolivia."},{"time":700000,"text":"And then after that, there are all sorts"},{"time":702000,"text":"of compounds and elements that we can extract,"},{"time":704000,"text":"like phosphates, that we need to get back into the desert soils to fertilize them."},{"time":707000,"text":"And there's just about every element of the periodic table"},{"time":709000,"text":"in seawater."},{"time":711000,"text":"So it should be possible to extract valuable elements"},{"time":713000,"text":"like lithium for high-performance batteries."},{"time":717000,"text":"And in parts of the Arabian Gulf,"},{"time":720000,"text":"the seawater, the salinity is increasing steadily"},{"time":723000,"text":"due to the discharge of waste brine"},{"time":725000,"text":"from desalination plants."},{"time":727000,"text":"And it's pushing the ecosystem close to collapse."},{"time":730000,"text":"Now we would be able to make use of all that waste brine."},{"time":732000,"text":"We could evaporate it"},{"time":734000,"text":"to enhance the restorative benefits"},{"time":736000,"text":"and capture the salts,"},{"time":738000,"text":"transforming an urgent waste problem into a big opportunity."},{"time":741000,"text":"Really the Sahara Forest Project is a model"},{"time":743000,"text":"for how we could create zero-carbon food,"},{"time":746000,"text":"abundant renewable energy in some of the most water-stressed parts of the planet"},{"time":749000,"text":"as well as reversing desertification in certain areas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753000,"text":"So returning to those big challenges that I mentioned at the beginning:"},{"time":756000,"text":"radical increases in resource efficiency,"},{"time":758000,"text":"closing loops and a solar economy."},{"time":760000,"text":"They're not just possible; they're critical."},{"time":763000,"text":"And I firmly believe that studying the way nature solves problems"},{"time":766000,"text":"will provide a lot of the solutions."},{"time":769000,"text":"But perhaps more than anything, what this thinking provides"},{"time":772000,"text":"is a really positive way of talking about sustainable design."},{"time":774000,"text":"Far too much of the talk about the environment"},{"time":776000,"text":"uses very negative language."},{"time":778000,"text":"But here it's about synergies and abundance and optimizing."},{"time":781000,"text":"And this is an important point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"Antoine de Saint-Exupery once said,"},{"time":785000,"text":"\"If you want to build a flotilla of ships,"},{"time":787000,"text":"you don't sit around talking about carpentry."},{"time":789000,"text":"No, you need to set people's souls ablaze"},{"time":792000,"text":"with visions of exploring distant shores.\""},{"time":794000,"text":"And that's what we need to do, so let's be positive,"},{"time":797000,"text":"and let's make progress with what could be"},{"time":799000,"text":"the most exciting period of innovation we've ever seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}